HEADWORD: Diminuendo
<hw>Di*min`u*en"do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[It., p. pr.
of <ets>diminuere</ets> to diminish.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>In a
gradually diminishing manner; with abatement of tone; decrescendo; --
expressed on the staff by <xex>Dim</xex>., or <xex>Dimin</xex>., or the
sign.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diminuent</ent>⟦br⟧
